# UAWSO daily automation - example crontab entry. NOT INSTALLED.
#
# This file is documentation only - copying it into an active crontab
# (`crontab -e` or a file under /etc/cron.d/) is a separate, explicit
# deployment step that this task does not perform.
#
# Schedule: 12:00 PM Asia/Colombo (UTC+05:30, no daylight saving), daily.
#
# Preferred form (cronie/Vixie cron with CRON_TZ support - most modern
# Linux distributions): set CRON_TZ so the schedule is correct even if the
# system's default timezone is not Asia/Colombo.
CRON_TZ=Asia/Colombo
0 12 * * * /path/to/project/05_IMPLEMENTATION/commands/update_for_today.sh >> /path/to/project/05_IMPLEMENTATION/runtime/uawso_daily/logs/cron.log 2>&1

# Fallback form, for cron daemons that do NOT support CRON_TZ (per-line or
# per-file): compute the fixed UTC offset yourself. Asia/Colombo is
# UTC+05:30 year-round, so 12:00 Colombo = 06:30 UTC. If the crontab's
# environment/system timezone is UTC, use:
# 30 6 * * * /path/to/project/05_IMPLEMENTATION/commands/update_for_today.sh >> /path/to/project/05_IMPLEMENTATION/runtime/uawso_daily/logs/cron.log 2>&1

# Notes:
# - Replace /path/to/project with the actual absolute deployment path.
# - The wrapper script itself sets its working directory - cron's default
#   minimal PATH/HOME is otherwise sufficient since python3 is invoked
#   directly (adjust the shebang/python3 path in update_for_today.sh if a
#   virtualenv or specific interpreter is required on the target host).
# - Database credentials must already exist in
#   05_IMPLEMENTATION/config/.env on the target host (git-ignored, NTFS/
#   POSIX-permission restricted) - this cron entry does not set or pass
#   any credential.
